                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2077: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-13T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 13, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>87. Your 188, October 13, noon. Your views therein are approved. If the League
                    Council should invite the United States to take part in its discussion of the
                    present Manchurian situation, authorization is <pb facs="0294" n="184"
                        xml:id="pg_184"/> given you to accept such invitation, to sit in any
                    discussion of this subject as an observer and auditor, and to participate in the
                    Council discussions when they relate to possible application of the Kellogg
                    Pact, of which treaty the United States is a signatory.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
